Author: msn <msn@polaris.dev>
Date:   Mon Jun 15 21:02:54 2026 -0700

    I-arch-007 re-gate iter1: close 4 residual fail-open P0s + 1 P1 (all stricter, faithfulness untouched)
    
    Codex re-gate (w82clbwhk) returned REQUEST_CHANGES on all 4 units — every residual a
    fail-open in the stricter/consolidate direction (zero faithfulness relaxation):
    
    RELEASE P0 #3: run_honest_sweep_r3.py:10980 reconstructed missing/malformed release proof as
      adjudicated=True. Flip to fail-CLOSED (default False) — legit releases always serialize
      release_disclosure["adjudicated"] (9889-9904), so this only bites the missing-proof hole.
    
    GEN P0: fact_dedup.py rewrite fallbacks (JSON-fail / shape-mismatch / per-item null) DROPPED
      corroborating cited sentences. Now KEEP-all (emit no drop key -> apply_rewrites keeps the
      original) per §-1.3 CONSOLIDATE-DON'T-DROP. A failed merge never deletes a corroborator.
    
    FETCH P0 (A17): contradiction_detector.py grouped by (subject,predicate,unit,dose) with no
      same-source guard. Add it: a cross-source contradiction needs >=2 distinct sources; a single-
      source span is labeled not_comparable, kept OUT of the headline count, every claim disclosed
      (never dropped). Mirrors the A17 commensurability pattern.
    
    SWEEP P0: iarch007_release_invariant_check.py demanded D8/seam proof only on strict statuses, so
      partial_saturation+release_allowed=true+empty final_verdicts slipped through. Extend the proof
      demand to every non-abort release (partial_*/unknown included).
    
    SWEEP P1: convert the two banned source-text-grep A4 proxy tests to behavioral — extract the pure
      build_attempted_zero_emit_section_stub helper (unit-callable) and test the real resolver count
      (resolve_provenance_to_citations_with_count([],{}) -> emitted_count==0, the is_gap_stub trigger).
    
    Tests: stale fact_dedup drop-on-failure tests -> keep-all contract; contradiction _ev fixtures ->
      distinct source_url per evidence_id (the old shared placeholder was an unrealistic artifact);
      +1 same-source-guard behavioral test; +3 partial-release SWEEP invariant tests. 159 + 31 green.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

